                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The accursed forge-spurned breathes a cloud of stinging soot, ash, and glowing embers. This can affect either a 30-foot cone or a 20-foot burst centered on the accursed forge-spurned and persists for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}. Creatures that move into or start their turn in the area take [[/r 12d6 #fire]]{12d6 fire damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect,divine,evocation,fire\" data-pf2-label=\"Forge Breath DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"36\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save).</p>\n<p>A creature that fails its save is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} for 1 minute. Creatures within the cloud are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Concealed]{Concealed}, though not from the accursed forge-spurned.</p>\n<p data-visibility=\"gm\">The accursed forge-spurned can't use Forge Breath again until it has used Inflate Bellows.</p>"
